{"title_page": "Shenelle Henry", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Shenelle Henry\n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|3|13|df=y}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.socawarriors.net/womens-team/womens-team-news/womens-u20/13492-t-t-clash-with-honduras-in-opening-u-20-conacaf-qualifier.html|title=T&T clash with Honduras in opening U-20 CONACAF qualifier|first=Shaun|last=Fuentes|website=Soca Warriors|date=9 January 2014|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = Trinidad and Tobago<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/shenelle-henry/375768/|title={{PAGENAME}}|website=Global Sports Archive|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n| height         = 1.60 m<ref name=WCA>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wileyathletics.com/sport/womens-soccer/2017-18/roster/shenelle-henry|title=Shenelle Henry 2017 Women's Soccer Roster |website=Wiley College Athletics|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]], [[midfielder]]<ref name=WCA/>\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Diego Martin North Secondary School\n| collegeyears1  = 2014\n| college1       = [[Cisco College|Cisco Wranglers]]\n| collegecaps1   = 12\n| collegegoals1  = 2\n| collegeyears2  = 2015\u20132017\n| college2       = [[Wiley College|Wiley Wildcats]]\n| collegecaps2   = 25\n| collegegoals2  = 8\n| years1         = \n| clubs1         = Real Dimension\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u20132018\n| nationalteam1  = [[Trinidad and Tobago women's national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = 10 October 2018\n}}\n'''Shenelle Henry''' (born 13 March 1994) is a Trinidad and Tobago [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]]. She has been a member of the [[Trinidad and Tobago women's national football team|Trinidad and Tobago women's national team]].\n\n==International career==\nHenry capped for Trinidad and Tobago at senior level during the [[Football at the 2015 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's tournament|2015 Pan American Games]] and the [[2018 CONCACAF Women's Championship]].<ref name=SW>{{soccerway|408079|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2018 CONCACAF Women's Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Henry, Shenelle}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Women's association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games competitors for Trinidad and Tobago]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2015 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:College women's soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Cisco College alumni]]\n[[Category:Wiley College alumni]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Expatriate women's soccer players in the United States]]\n\n\n{{Trinidad-footy-bio-stub}}\n{{Caribbean-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Shenelle Henry\n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|3|13|df=y}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.socawarriors.net/womens-team/womens-team-news/womens-u20/13492-t-t-clash-with-honduras-in-opening-u-20-conacaf-qualifier.html|title=T&T clash with Honduras in opening U-20 CONACAF qualifier|first=Shaun|last=Fuentes|website=Soca Warriors|date=9 January 2014|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = Trinidad and Tobago<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/shenelle-henry/375768/|title={{PAGENAME}}|website=Global Sports Archive|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n| height         = 1.60 m<ref name=WCA>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wileyathletics.com/sport/womens-soccer/2017-18/roster/shenelle-henry|title=Shenelle Henry 2017 Women's Soccer Roster |website=Wiley College Athletics|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]], [[midfielder]]<ref name=WCA/>\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Diego Martin North Secondary School\n| collegeyears1  = 2014\n| college1       = [[Cisco College|Cisco Wranglers]]\n| collegecaps1   = 12\n| collegegoals1  = 2\n| collegeyears2  = 2015\u20132017\n| college2       = [[Wiley College|Wiley Wildcats]]\n| collegecaps2   = 25\n| collegegoals2  = 8\n| years1         = \n| clubs1         = Real Dimension\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u20132018\n| nationalteam1  = [[Trinidad and Tobago women's national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = 10 October 2018\n}}\n'''Shenelle Henry''' (born 13 March 1994) is a Trinidad and Tobago [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]]. She has been a member of the [[Trinidad and Tobago women's national football team|Trinidad and Tobago women's national team]].\n\n==International career==\nHenry capped for Trinidad and Tobago at senior level during the [[Football at the 2015 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's tournament|2015 Pan American Games]] and the [[2018 CONCACAF Women's Championship]].<ref name=SW>{{soccerway|408079|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2018 CONCACAF Women's Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Henry, Shenelle}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Women's association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games competitors for Trinidad and Tobago]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2015 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:College women's soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Cisco College alumni]]\n[[Category:Wiley College alumni]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Expatriate women's soccer players in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shenelle_Henry"}
{"title_page": "Urfi Javed", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Urfi Javed\n| image =\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth-date and age|15 October 1997}}\n| birth_place = [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| other_names = \n| occupation = [[Model (person)|Model]]<br>[[Actress]]<br>[[rapper]]\n| known_for = ''[[Bepannaah]]''\n}}\n\n'''Urfi Javed''' is an Indian television actress. She is known for portraying the role of Avni in ''[[Bade Bhaiyya Ki Dulhania]]'', Aarti in ''[[Meri Durga]]'' and Bella in ''[[Bepannah]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nBorn and brought up in Lucknow, Urfi did her schooling from [[City Montessori School]] and then did her mass communication from Amity University. She was working in Delhi as an assistant to a fashion designer and then came to Mumbai. She opposes religion and says \"I know the pain of being born in a Muslim family. We girls bury our dreams.\"<ref>{{cite AV media\n | people =\n | date = 15 February 2020\n | title = urf7i\n | trans-title =\n | medium =\n | language = English\n | url = \n | access-date =\n | archive-url =\n | archive-date =\n | format = Status Photograph\n | time = 11:30 pm\n | location = \n | publisher = Instagram\n | id = \n | isbn =\n | oclc =\n | quote =\n | ref =\n}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2016, Javed appeared in [[Sony TV]]'s ''[[Bade Bhaiyya Ki Dulhania]]'' as Avni Pant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/videos/tv/hindi/urfi-javed-hot-photos-sexy-video-actress-urfi-javed-sets-hearts-racing-with-these-bold-pictures/videoshow/72475632.cms|title=Urfi Javed sets hearts racing with these bold pictures|last=|first=|date=|website=Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> From 2016 to 2017, she played Chhaya in [[Star Plus]]'s ''[[Chandra Nandini]]''. Then, she portrayed Aarti in [[Star Plus]]'s ''[[Meri Durga]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/meri-durga-actors-urfi-javed-and-vicky-ahuja-join-tv-s-daayan-launch-date-revealed-181119|title=Meri Durga actors Urfi Javed and Vicky Ahuja join &TV's Daayan|website=Tellychakkar|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, she played Kamini Joshi in [[SAB TV]]'s ''[[Saat Phero Ki Hera Pherie]],'' Bella Kapoor in [[Colors TV]]'s ''[[Bepannaah]]'', Piyali in [[Star Bharat]]'s ''[[Jiji Maa]]'' and Nandini in [[&TV]]'s ''[[Daayan (TV series)|Daayan]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/soaps/story/this-actress-is-all-set-to-enter-jennifer-winget-and-harshad-chopda-s-bepannaah-1200389-2018-03-29|title=This actress is all set to enter Jennifer Winget and Harshad Chopda's Bepannaah|website=India Today|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/charu-asopa-replaces-urfi-javed-in-jiji-maa/articleshow/65656143.cms|title=Charu Asopa replaces Urfi Javed in 'Jiji Maa'|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, she joined ''[[Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai]]'' as Shivani Bhatia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/entertainment/television/yeh-rishta-kya-kehlata-hai-bepannaah-actress-urfi-javed-to-enter-as-trishas-laweyer-in-shivangi-joshi-mohsin-khans-show-1164072|title=Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai: Urfi Javed to enter as Trisha's lawyer|last=|first=|date=|website=ABP Live|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Next, she played Tanisha Chakraborty in ''[[Kasautii Zindagii Kay (2018 TV series)|Kasautii Zindagii Kay]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/entertainment/television/kasautii-zindagii-kay-2-yeh-rishta-kya-kehlata-hai-actress-urfi-javed-to-enter-parth-samthaan-erica-fernandess-show-1168769|title=Urfi Javed to enter Kasautii Zindagii Kay post leap|last=|first=|date=|website=ABP Live|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-alig